post_text: Uniforms will be issued on Monday. This is always a big day for First State Military Academy. Each new Cadet will be issued their MARPATS (which stands for Marine Pattern uniform). They will be shown how to properly wear the uniform, how the cover should sit on the head, how to roll their sleeves (harder than it looks!), how to blouse the trousers and they will learn the rules, regulations and expectations when in uniform.

RAIDERS SCHOLARSHIP AWARDED: Congratulations to Cadet Dunning and Cadet Andrews for being the first cadets to be awarded the Raiders Scholarship. They will both be receiving $1000.

To be eligible for the scholarship, a cadet must be on the Raiders for two plus years, 2.5 GPA,, participate in competitions and volunteer at Raiders events. This Scholarship was made possible by Anthem Planning.

Congratulations to Cadets Dunning and Andrews and thank you Anthem Planning!

post_text:
CLASS OF 2020:

To return your Chromebook and charger, we will have the following Drop-Off times:

Tuesday, May 26th from 3pm to 7pm
Wednesday, May 27th from 9am to 12pm

You do not need to sign up ahead of time. This will be a drive-thru drop off. No one will be permitted to leave their vehicle. You will drive up in front of Drexel Hall and a staff member will come to your car, hand you a paper that you will sign saying you have returned your Chromebook and charger (if applicable), and then sign. Then you will put the paper inside your Chromebook and put it and your charger in a box that the staff member will be holding.

Following CDC guidelines, we ask that all individuals in the car wear a mask while your car windows are down and you are interacting with others. Staff members will be wearing masks and gloves. Chromebooks will only be directly handled by the person returning it. Once the Chromebook is in the box, it will be held in storage and disinfected at a later date.

Congratulations to C/Gaeta.

Cadet Raven Gaeta is this years Clayton Lions Club Julian Dunning Scholarship winner.

Julian Dunning was a charter member of the Clayton Club and was always working to make things better for the young people of the community. So therefore the Clayton Lions Club created the scholarship on behalf of his name. When the scholarship was created areas that the club takes a look at are Grade point average, extracurricular activities (in school) and extracurricular activities (in the community) as well as accomplishments from the last two years.

Clayton, Delaware Lions Club

post_text:
2020 YEARBOOKS HAVE ARRRIVED!!! Distribution of the books will begin next week starting with the senior class. Seniors should pick-up their books using curb-side pickup in front of St. Michael’s Hall immediately prior to their designated time to turn-in their uniforms. Only Senior Yearbooks will distributed next week.

Underclass Yearbook Distribution will take place on May 11 and 12 from 9 a.m. until 7 p.m. Yearbook Advisors will provide curb side pick-up in front of St. Michael’s Hall during this time. No appointment is necessary.

NOTE – The distribution will follow current CDC and State of Delaware guidelines to prevent the spread of the COVID-19 virus. Cadets and/or parents should NOT leave their vehicles. Advisors will bring the books to them.

A limited number of Yearbooks can still be purchased by going to www.jostensyearbooks.com. Yearbooks sales has been brisk – with almost 20 sold in the past several weeks. Here are a few pictures of the book.

If you have any questions, please contact Mr. Bates (dbates@fsmilitary.org) or Mrs. Cook (acook@fsmilitary.org).

Senior Highlight: Cole Pope

Cole was a member of the lacrosse team as well as the wrestling team. His favorite thing about lacrosse is when he makes a play on defense and avoids being hit by the attackman. Senior Highlight: Tyler Jenkins

Tyler has been a member of the baseball team for four years and a captain for three. Food Assistance Update‼️

Food Distribution will begin tomorrow, Wednesday March 18th. Grab and Go meals will be served daily Monday – Friday from 11:00 am – 12:30 pm. Service locations are:
📍Banneker Elementary School
📍Morris Early Childhood Center
📍Mispillion Elementary School
📍Mt. Zion Church in Ellendale

We are pleased to announce due to community donations, we will also be able to give adults who accompany students with a meal, free of charge.
Please remember that we are practicing social distancing. If you have any questions please email info@msd.k12.de.us.

Additionally, there are several Milford businesses who have offered to provide free meals to our students during this time. Businesses include Nancy's Cafe on Walnut, My Sister's Fault, and Westside Restaurant.

shared_text:
Nancy's Cafe on Walnut
March 14 at 9:24 AM ·

Milford schools are closing for two weeks and I believe there will be more community-wide closings soon. Our youngest citizens and their families will need our help during this time. The most important assistance we can give is to ensure they have good, healthy food to keep up their immunities and fill any gaps in their nutrition.

Beginning Tuesday, March 17th NANCY’S CAFÉ at 22 So. Walnut Street will offer our housemade soups and bread free of charge to anyone who walks in our door from 11 am to 3 pm. We will continue this until the need no longer exists. You can have a seat with us or take it out. If you are uncomfortable being in a public place at this time we will bring the food to the door. Just know that we follow strict sanitary procedures and wipe down all surfaces with disinfectant on a regular basis. MILFORD STRONG!

My Sister's Fault
March 14 at 3:45 AM ·

****** UPDATED POST******
First we want to thank everyone for your suggestions, comments and advised. At the end of the day what matter is our intentions to help those IN NEED!!!!! Because we been there, we know what is like growing up depending on school lunches to have a meal.

Our new plan is as follows:

1. PARK IN FRONT OF OUR BAKERY (WED, THUR & FRIDAY 9AM-4PM)
2. WE WILL HAVE A VOLUNTEER OUTSIDE WAITING FOR YOU
3. WE WILL PROVIDE ONE MEAL PER KID IN THE CAR. (no exceptions)
4. NO NEED TO GET OUT OF THE CAR, WE WILL BRING THE MEALS TO YOU.
6. NO PURCHASE REQUIRED
7. WE WILL BE OFFERING ONE MEAL OPTION A DAY (instead of multiple options) TO ENSURE OUR REGULAR BUSINESS OPERATIONS ARE NOT AFFECTED.
8. WE HAVE A LIMITED SUPPLY OF 200 MEALS A DAY.

ORIGINAL POST----->Delaware schools are closing for the next two weeks. My Sister’s Fault will be offering School Age Kids a free meal Wed-Fri (for the next two weeks) during our hours of operation.

Courtesy of MSF...
(Kids must be present at the time of ordering, food can be take out)

Are you interested in doing something different and meeting new people? Would you be interested in attending a cake decorating event? This would not be a fundraiser. Whatever the vendor charges per person is what each participant would pay. The PSO would cover the cost of snacks and beverages.

If you would be interested in a decorating/casual social event and the cost would be $40, drop me a comment and if we have enough interest, we will schedule the event. Each participant would make and take home a cake similar to the one I have pictured. (We have other cake options also!) I would want to schedule on a Saturday afternoon or a Sunday.

post_text:
Juniors: Are you interested in attending the US Naval Academy? Consider joining their Summer Seminar. Applications opened on January 3, 2020.

https://www.usna.edu/Admissions/Programs/NASS.php#fndtn-panel1-Steps-For

"The United States Naval Academy Summer Seminar is the first step in navigating your future to becoming one of our nation's next generation of leaders.

If you are currently in your junior year of high school and considering the Naval Academy as your college of choice, we strongly recommend you consider applying to Summer Seminar. Summer Seminar will introduce you to life at the Academy, where you will experience first-class academic, athletic, and professional training at the #1 public college in the U.S.* (Top 25 Public College in the U.S. 2017, Forbes). Your Summer Seminar application will also serve as a preliminary application to the Academy that you will complete before or during your senior year.

You will live in Bancroft Hall, experience life on The Yard and learn from some of our best midshipmen and most esteemed faculty."

post_text:
Update on registration for these classes. In order to prepare for the number attending please call the school office with your RSVP. 302-223-2150. Although numerous people indicated interest (which was the reason for starting the classes) only (2) have RSVP’ed by e-mail. Thank you!

Cadets may indicate they are attending by letting the office know after confirming their attendance with parent permission.

The Basic Defensive Driving Class is Saturday, November 9, 2019 (Not 11/23/19) from 0900-1600 (9:00am-4:00pm)

The Advanced or Refresher Defensive Driving Class is the same as stated - November 23, 2019 from 0900-1200 (9:00am-Noon).

For any questions please contact Officer Hibbert at Michael.Hibbert@cj.state.de.us
